    "time_limit": null,
    "feedback": "The formula for the total surface area, <i>A<\/i>, of a right prism whose base area<br> \r\nis <i>B<\/i> and whose slant height is <i>s<\/i> is: <math>\r\n <mrow>\r\n  <mi>A<\/mi><mo>=<\/mo><mfrac>\r\n   <mn>1<\/mn>\r\n   <mn>2<\/mn>\r\n  <\/mfrac>\r\n  <mi>p<\/mi><mi>s<\/mi><mo>+<\/mo><mi>B<\/mi><\/mrow>\r\n<\/math>\r\n<\/br> \r\n<p><\/p>\r\nThe base has an area of <i>B<\/i> = 144 square inches. So, each side of the square<br>\r\nbase has a length of <math>\r\n <mrow>\r\n  <msqrt>\r\n   <mrow>\r\n    <mn>144<\/mn><\/mrow>\r\n  <\/msqrt>\r\n  <\/mrow>\r\n<\/math> = 12 inches. So, the perimeter of the base is <i>p<\/i> = 48 inches. \r\nThe slant height of the candle is <i>s<\/i> = 10 inches.\r\n<p><\/p>\r\nSubstitute these values into the formula:\r\n<p><\/p>\r\n<math>\r\n <mrow>\r\n  <mi>A<\/mi><mo>=<\/mo><mfrac>\r\n   <mn>1<\/mn>\r\n   <mn>2<\/mn>\r\n  <\/mfrac>\r\n  <mrow><mo>(<\/mo>\r\n   <mrow>\r\n    <mn>48<\/mn><\/mrow>\r\n  <mo>)<\/mo><\/mrow><mrow><mo>(<\/mo>\r\n   <mrow>\r\n    <mn>10<\/mn><\/mrow>\r\n  <mo>)<\/mo><\/mrow><mo>+<\/mo><mn>144<\/mn><mo>=<\/mo><mn>240<\/mn><mo>+<\/mo><mn>144<\/mn><mo>=<\/mo><mn>384<\/mn><\/mrow>\r\n<\/math>\r\n<p><\/p>\r\n<b>The total surface area of the candle is 384 square inches.<\/b>\r\n",
